    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A basketball fan wants to create a visualization to show the difference between home and visiting team scores. For example, if the home team scored 75 and the visiting team scored 64, the visual should show 11.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">BasketballScene.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getScoreDiff()</code> method. This method should:\r\n\r\n1. Take two <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">int</code> parameters: the home team score and the visiting team score.\r\n\r\n2. Return the absolute value of the difference between the two scores.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getScoreDiff()</code> method with multiple sets of scores and pass the result to the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResult()</code> method.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.abs(home - visitor)</code> to calculate the score difference.\r\n</div>\r\n",
